By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Africa’s most populous nation – Nigeria has recorded 1,270 new cases of COVID-19, its Centre for Disease Control said on Monday. The report released via NCDC’s twitter handle stated that the fresh infections were recorded from 22 states including the FCT. Lagos State led the infection table with 435 cases followed by FCT with 234 while Oyo came third with 103. Other states where infections were recorded in heirachical sequence are; Plateau-86; Rivers-71; Enugu-51; Nasarawa-41; Delta and Edo-39; Osun-33; Niger-31;Sokoto-23; Ondo-16; Taraba-13; Ebonyi-12;Kano-10; Abia-9; Bayelsa-8; Bauchi-7; Imo-5;Katsina-3 and Gombe-1. The health agency gave the breakdown of the total confirmed cases as stated below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Precise Post) -   The national health agency in charge of COVID-19, Nigeria Centre for  Disease Control on Tuesday announced the confirmation of 296 new cases of the novel virus in the country. The agency reported that the new infections were recorded in 15 states of the… September 9, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Lagos State - the epicentre of COVID-19 in the country accounted for 225 infections as Nigeria recorded 617 new cases of on Saturday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. According to the the report released via the agency's twitter handle, other… December 13, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the large… October 31, 2020 In "Top Stories"